(lock clicks)

262
00:10:19,536 --> 00:10:20,116
‐ Huh?

263
00:10:20,203 --> 00:10:20,953
Hey.

264
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:21,909
Hey, wait a minute.

265
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,456
Why did you just lock the door?

266
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:25,211
I thought you wanted to
talk to me about something.

267
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:27,711
‐ Yes, something very private.

268
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:28,964
‐ Something private?

269
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:31,207
‐ I know that you’re entering
the upcoming art competition.

270
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:32,797
‐ I am?

271
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:34,974
‐ And I was hoping that
you’d use me as your subject.

272
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,011
‐ Oh, okay.

273
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:37,006
Since this is all make believe,

274
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:38,547
I guess I can swallow that.

275
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:41,598
Well, I’m very
flattered by your offer.

276
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:43,143
‐ You know...

277
00:10:43,268 --> 00:10:44,888
(clothes ruffling)

278
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:47,558
(bells chiming)

279
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:50,645
(gasping)

280
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,653
I wouldn’t do this
for anyone but you.

281
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:53,567
(gasps)

282
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,613
‐ No, you can’t do that, Megumi.

283
00:10:55,697 --> 00:10:57,197
I mean, we’re still
high school students.

284
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:59,453
And we’re just not
old enough yet.

285
00:10:59,534 --> 00:11:02,504
(wind harshly blowing)

286
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:03,789
‐ [Ruri] We’re all
clear, Captain.

287
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:04,912
No obstacles ahead.

288
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:06,368
Switching to Autopilot.

289
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:08,790
Um, Captain?

290
00:11:08,877 --> 00:11:10,627
‐ Huh?
‐ Everyone’s gone to lunch.

291
00:11:10,712 --> 00:11:12,252
Aren’t you feeling hungry, yet?

292
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,008
‐ Oh, I’m fine.

293
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,010
Why don’t you go ahead, Ruri.

294
00:11:15,091 --> 00:11:16,011
‐ Sure.

295
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:27,018
‐ Akito, do you love her too?

296
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:28,353
‐ Stop it.

297
00:11:28,438 --> 00:11:30,438
‐ Why are you so angry at me?

298
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:31,573
I know that you like me.

299
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:33,151
You took my first kiss.

300
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:34,614
‐ That’s just a
little different.

301
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,864
Will you please put
your clothes back on?

302
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:39,316
‐ Don’t you care about
me anymore, Akito?

303
00:11:40,617 --> 00:11:41,157
‐ Huh?

304
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:41,952
Well...

305
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:43,295
I of course.

306
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,749
‐ Because the truth is
that I love you, Akito.

307
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:46,622
I do.

308
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,461
‐ Oh, Megumi...

309
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,042
‐ If the two of them...

310
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:53,047
If Akito and Megumi are...

311
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:55,009
If they...

312
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:56,719
(gasps)
I won’t believe it.

313
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,679
(machine beep)

314
00:11:57,759 --> 00:12:00,299
(computer alarms)
(Captain gasps)

315
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,136
Oops.

316
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:03,971
(ship whirring)

317
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:11,059
‐ Please kiss me.

318
00:12:11,189 --> 00:12:11,479
‐ Megumi, I...

319
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:16,823
‐ I just want something that
means there’s still hope.

320
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:17,863
‐ Yurika?
‐ Huh?

321
00:12:17,946 --> 00:12:18,896
(Akito yells)

322
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:21,700
(alarms blaring)

323
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:24,656
‐ It’s a full squadron alert.

324
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:26,454
That means we must
be under attack!

325
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:29,499
(lasers blasting)

326
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,333
‐ Maintain our
shields and retreat.

327
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:34,088
‐ The distortion field
is holding steady.

328
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,130
‐ 10 more seconds ’till
we’re out of their range.

329
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:37,126
‐ [Ruri] Gravity
sensors indicate

330
00:12:37,257 --> 00:12:39,007
numerous high
mobile enemy units.

331
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:41,092
‐ How far are we going
to pull back, Captain?

332
00:12:41,219 --> 00:12:42,259
‐ Weigh our options.

333
00:12:42,387 --> 00:12:45,637
(overlapping chatter)

334
00:12:47,225 --> 00:12:50,445
(happy fanfare music)

335
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:54,057
(ships whirring)

336
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,478
(wind harshly blowing)

337
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:03,281
‐ [Rori] These are the
enemy numbers and positions

338
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:05,656
as indicated by our
magnetic resonance scan.

339
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:07,445
‐ Of course, they all know
where we are now, too.

340
00:13:07,537 --> 00:13:08,787
Thanks to the captain

341
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:10,461
and that stupidity with
the gravity cannon.

342
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:12,290
‐ Well, there’s no sense
crying over spilled milk.

343
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:13,747
(scoffs)

344
00:13:13,835 --> 00:13:15,095
‐ What was that?
‐ Why worry about something

345
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:16,049
you can’t change (chuckles)?

346
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:19,259
‐ Sysis my responsibility.

347
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,800
If someone is to be
help responsible,

348
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:23,143
it would be me for
leaving my post.

349
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:24,139
I apologize.

350
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,390
(guffaws)

351
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:27,261
‐ Could it be that
cool and logical Ruri

352
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:28,428
is actually covering
for the captain?

353
00:13:28,516 --> 00:13:30,426
‐ Has she discovered
her human feelings?

354
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:31,808
‐ Idiots.

355
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:33,484
‐ Since we were detected
in the Western Passage,

356
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,234
we’ll have to try to sneak in

357
00:13:35,315 --> 00:13:37,275
through the Eastern
Island Straits.

358
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:39,188
We’ll have to fly in
at a low altitude,

359
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:41,819
at a 72% chance of
running aground.

360
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:44,446
Unfortunately, I’m afraid
that that’s our best option.

361
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:46,332
‐ The Nadesico will
embark in 10 minutes

362
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:48,199
and will proceed through
the Eastern Passage.

363
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:51,328
Aestivalis units are to
stand by at alert status.

364
00:13:51,414 --> 00:13:52,674
That’s all.

365
00:13:52,749 --> 00:13:53,669
‐ I wonder what
happened to the Captain?

366
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:57,631
‐ Maybe she snuck off
some place to cry.

367
00:13:57,712 --> 00:13:59,512
‐ I’ll be right back!

368
00:13:59,589 --> 00:14:01,299
‐ Hey, wait up, Tenkawa!

369
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:01,592
Sheesh.

370
00:14:04,302 --> 00:14:07,352
(solemn piano music)

371
00:14:07,472 --> 00:14:08,512
‐ Yurika...

372
00:14:09,766 --> 00:14:11,226
(groans)

373
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:14,141
(machine whirring)
(gasps)

374
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:15,098
‐ Akito!

375
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:16,058
‐ Yurika...

376
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:19,688
(buzzing)

377
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,122
This might sound kinda
strange coming from me,

378
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:37,378
but I get worried when
you’re not all spastic.

379
00:14:37,460 --> 00:14:40,880
It’s just not like you to be
acting serious and responsible.

380
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:41,883
‐ Akito.

381
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,014
Help me.

382
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:43,881
‐ Huh?

383
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:46,889
‐ Help me, please.

384
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:49,392
I don’t know who else
to turn to anymore

385
00:14:49,472 --> 00:14:51,272
except you, Akito.

386
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:52,931
I’m such a clutz

387
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,269
and I keep messing this
up for everyone else.

388
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:56,690
Or do you hate me now too?

389
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:04,856
(crying)
I’m sorry.

390
00:15:04,946 --> 00:15:06,196
I shouldn’t.

391
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,820
‐ I just want something that
means there’s still hope.

392
00:15:14,372 --> 00:15:16,212
(gasps)

393
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:18,290
‐ I’m...

394
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:20,248
I know a trick that’ll help.

395
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:21,246
Yurika...

396
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:28,303
‐ Hold it.

397
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:29,548
You’re not doing this

398
00:15:29,637 --> 00:15:31,507
because you feel
sorry for me, are you?

399
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:32,767
‐ Excuse me?

400
00:15:32,849 --> 00:15:34,019
‐ I know that when
we were on Mars,

401
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,190
I asked for a kiss to
help me keep going.

402
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:37,689
But you didn’t kiss me

403
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:39,860
because you knew I had to
find the strength myself.

404
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:40,939
‐ Huh?

405
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:42,523
‐ At the time, I
didn’t understand why.

406
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:43,608
But afterwards,
it all made sense.

407
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:46,204
You know me better
than I know myself.

408
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:49,069
And I know you’d never waste
something this precious.

409
00:15:49,824 --> 00:15:51,204
‐ Um, waste what?

410
00:15:52,702 --> 00:15:53,702
‐ Oh, Akito.

411
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:57,249
I know you know I’ve
never been kissed before.

412
00:15:57,331 --> 00:15:59,331
(gasps)
(bell chimes)

413
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:00,669
‐ Wait a second.

414
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:01,293
What do you mean,
"Never been kissed?"

415
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:02,287
‐ Mm‐hmm.

416
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:03,590
I’m waiting for true love.

417
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:05,381
‐ You don’t remember?

418
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:07,805
(gasps)
(alarms blaring)

419
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:09,644
‐ It’s another enemy attack!

420
00:16:09,719 --> 00:16:10,839
I guess that means

421
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:11,680
we’ll have to continue
some other time.

422
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:12,644
Won’t we, Akito?

423
00:16:12,722 --> 00:16:14,352
‐ Yeah, sure, whatever.

424
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:19,314
(ships roaring)
(tense music)

425
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:20,345
(lasers blasting)

426
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,810
‐ Well, look who’s back.

427
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:23,820
‐ I’m sorry I’m late.

428
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,281
May I have the status
report, please?

429
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:27,569
‐ We are currently passing
through the Island Reefs.

430
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,113
‐ You know, it
would be very nice

431
00:16:29,197 --> 00:16:30,817
if you could just hurry
up and get on with it

432
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:32,948
so our investigator
won’t starve to death.

433
00:16:33,034 --> 00:16:34,414
‐ So that he won’t
starve to death?

434
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:36,704
‐ But wouldn’t he be more
likely to freeze to death

435
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:37,789
under these kind of
weather conditions?

436
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:40,252
‐ No, not with all that
insulating body fat.

437
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,253
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

438
00:16:42,502 --> 00:16:43,592
‐ Look, just hurry
up and get him.

439
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:44,379
(screams)

440
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:46,964
(rapid explosions)

441
00:16:47,048 --> 00:16:48,468
‐ Yurika, can you give
me the coordinates

442
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:49,969
where the investigator’s
supposed to be?

443
00:16:50,051 --> 00:16:50,761
‐ Coordinates?

444
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,393
‐ [Akito] Yurika, come on.

445
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:54,892
Proceed to map coordinates A‐13.

446
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,274
Ryoko, you and the others
will form a defensive screen.

447
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:58,140
‐ Rodger.

448
00:16:58,226 --> 00:17:01,146
(machines blasting)

449
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:06,032
‐ Hey, try not to steal
all the good scenes, okay?

450
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:07,278
‐ If you’re so hung
up on the captain,

451
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,150
you should welcome escort duty.

452
00:17:09,237 --> 00:17:10,697
(chuckles)

453
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:14,450
(heroic music)
(lasers blasting)

454
00:17:14,534 --> 00:17:19,294
(machines whirring)
(gun fire)

455
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:20,332
‐ Here we go.

456
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:22,004
Buttercup formation.

457
00:17:29,257 --> 00:17:31,377
(waves crashing)

458
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:32,757
(yelling)

459
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:39,017
(machine beeping)

460
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:39,680
‐ All right.

461
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:40,637
Where is he?

462
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:41,806
(gasps)

463
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:45,234
(ship engines roaring)

464
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:47,820
Damn it.

465
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,070
I’m almost at the edge of
the Nadesico’s energy range.

466
00:17:50,152 --> 00:17:51,322
Oh, crap.

467
00:17:51,404 --> 00:17:53,074
The blizzard must be
blocking the transmission.

468
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,405
(engine roaring)

469
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,870
(gun fire)

470
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,540
Man, I can’t see a thing

471
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:03,873
with all this snow
blowing around.

472
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:05,378
Hey, wait a second.

473
00:18:05,459 --> 00:18:07,709
Let’s try something that
doesn’t have to be aimed.

474
00:18:09,547 --> 00:18:10,457
Eat this!

475
00:18:11,549 --> 00:18:12,879
(gun fire)

476
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:20,807
Flare!

477
00:18:23,603 --> 00:18:26,273
(loud explosion)

478
00:18:29,317 --> 00:18:30,107
‐ Akito?

479
00:18:31,569 --> 00:18:32,489
‐ Akito...

480
00:18:33,613 --> 00:18:34,403
‐ He’ll be back.

481
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,738
I’m sure of it.

482
00:18:35,823 --> 00:18:37,453
(loud machine whirring)

483
00:18:37,575 --> 00:18:38,455
‐ Where’s Tinkawa?

484
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:40,704
‐ He’s taking his sweet time.

485
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:40,946
He’ll be back.

486
00:18:43,581 --> 00:18:44,501
‐ I see.

487
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:47,631
‐ Ryoko.
‐ Don’t give up yet, Ryoko.

488
00:18:47,752 --> 00:18:49,002
‐ I won’t.

489
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,378
I know he wouldn’t dare
break this girl’s heart.

490
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:55,799
‐ I’m afraid that it’s hopeless.

491
00:18:55,885 --> 00:18:57,145
‐ Even at full power,

492
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:58,759
he should be able to fly
for another 15 seconds.

493
00:18:58,846 --> 00:19:00,716
‐ Electromagnetic
static lifting,

494
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:03,426
radio transmission
is now possible.

495
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:07,190
(wind howling)

496
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:13,490
‐ No Aestivalis I
dentification signal detected.

497
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,149
‐ No incoming transmissions.

498
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:15,987
‐ Akito.

499
00:19:17,615 --> 00:19:19,535
‐ Oh, our poor investigator.

500
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:21,293
Oh well.

501
00:19:23,746 --> 00:19:25,456
‐ He’s gone.

502
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:27,039
And it’s all my fault.

503
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,166
I sent him out to a
cold, lonely death!

504
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:32,711
‐ [Akito] Um, not really.
(Yurika gasps)

505
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:33,668
‐ Akito!

506
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:34,718
‐ [Akito] Can you come get me?

507
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,510
‐ But just where are you?

508
00:19:36,634 --> 00:19:37,474
‐ [Akito] Down here.

509
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:38,761
(gasps)

510
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:41,514
(heroic music)

511
00:19:42,932 --> 00:19:44,272
(Yurika giggles)

512
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:46,020
‐ You really are okay!

513
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:48,523
‐ [Akito] Well, I’m
in one piece, anyway.

514
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:49,944
But admiral,

515
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,572
please don’t tell me this
is the special investigator

516
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:53,531
you were talking about.

517
00:19:53,651 --> 00:19:55,361
(bear roars)

518
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:58,114
‐ Well, I suppose you’re
wondering about that.

519
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:00,027
You see, the military
spent a lot of money

520
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:02,446
equipping that bear with all
those sensitive instruments.

521
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:03,955
But we knew that no one
would risk their life

522
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:07,206
to rescue a bear so we
named him, "Ambassador."

523
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:08,961
It was just a little white
lie, Captain (laughs).

524
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:14,341
(elevator whirring)

525
00:20:14,422 --> 00:20:15,592
‐ Oh, that God, Akito.

526
00:20:15,715 --> 00:20:17,515
I’m so glad you’re all right.

527
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,551
I was so worried about
what might’ve happened.

528
00:20:19,677 --> 00:20:21,137
‐ I’m sorry,

529
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,970
but I need to report back
to the Captain first.

530
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:25,684
(footsteps)

531
00:20:25,766 --> 00:20:27,886
(scoffs)

532
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,572
‐ Pilot Tenkawa
reporting, Captain.

533
00:20:38,696 --> 00:20:40,156
‐ Well done, pilot.

534
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,489
(giggles)

535
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:43,704
I mean thank you, Akito, dear.

536
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:45,794
(gasps)

537
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:48,081
‐ Has she really
forgotten our first kiss?

538
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:49,575
‐ Hmm?

539
00:20:49,707 --> 00:20:51,377
‐ Oh, nothing (chuckles).

540
00:20:51,459 --> 00:20:53,629
(laughter)

541
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:02,143
